    edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.Sendable, java.lang.AutoCloseable
    public class Climbing
extends edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem
    Controls the functions of the climbing subsystem. This system has pneumatics that moves its pivot points and motors that move it up and down.

        public void initDefaultCommand()
        Description copied from class: edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem
        Initialize the default command for a subsystem By default subsystems have no default command, but if they do, the default command is set with this method. It is called on all Subsystems by CommandBase in the users program after all the Subsystems are created.
        Specified by:
        initDefaultCommand in class edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem

      • setSpeed

        public void setSpeed​(double speed)
        Sets the speed of the climbing lift to a percentage between 1 and -1. Values < 0 move the system down Values > 0 move the system up
        Parameters:
        speed - The speed at which the motors are to be run.
